'''''Space Station 3D''''' (simply known as '''''Space Station''''' in 2D format) is a 2002 Canadian-American [[List of 3D films|3D]] [[Short film|short]] [[documentary film]] about the [[International Space Station]] written, produced, edited and directed by [[Toni Myers]].<ref>http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/space_station/</ref> Narrated by [[Tom Cruise]], it is the first [[IMAX 3D]] production filmed in space.

==Content==
''Space Station 3D'' was the first 3D live-action film to be shot in space. Using advanced 3D technology, the film tells the story of the greatest engineering feat since a man landed on the Moon; the on-orbit assembly of the International Space Station as it travels 220 miles above the Earth at 17,500&nbsp;mph. The film included sequences that portray the force of a rocket launch, look into the depths of space, experience life in zero gravity and accompany astronauts on a space walk."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sciencemuseum.org.uk/visitmuseum/events/imax_films/space_station_3d.aspx |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-04-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120414135759/http://www.sciencemuseum.org.uk/visitmuseum/events/imax_films/space_station_3d.aspx |archivedate=April 14, 2012 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>

==Release==
The film is the highest-grossing film never to have placed in the top 10 domestic box office, grossing $93,269,403 domestically and $34,463,670 overseas for a total worldwide gross of $127,733,073.<ref>{{cite web|title=Top Grossing Movies That Never Hit the Top 10 at the Box Office|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/alltime/domestic/never1.htm?page=never10&p=.htm|work=[[Box Office Mojo]]|publisher=[[Amazon.com]]|accessdate=2015-06-07}}</ref>

==Reception==
''Space Station 3D'' has received positive reviews. On [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film has a rating of 87%, based on 23 reviews, with an average rating of 6.9/10.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/space_station/|title=Space Station|work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=August 4, 2015}}</ref> [[Metacritic]] gives the film a score of 69 out of 100, based on 13 critics, indicating "generally favorable reviews".<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/space-station-3d | title=Space Station 3D | work=[[Metacritic]] | publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] | accessdate=August 4, 2015}}</ref>

